GOVERNMENT OF INDIA
CABINET SECRETARIAT
New Delhi, the 29th March, 1958.
The under signed is directed to say that Shri Lal Bahadur
Shastri has taken over charge of the Ministry of Commerce &
Industry from Shri Morarji R. Desai with effect from the
afternoon of the 28th March, 1968 and Shri S.K. Patil has
taken over charge of the Ministry of Transport & Communications
from Shri Lal Bahadur Shastri with effect from the forenoon of
the 29th March, 1958.
Shri Patil will however, continue to hold charge of the
Ministry of Irrigation & Power until Shri Hafiz Mohd Ibrahim
assumes office.
158-
IMMEDIATE
for information.
Nashchandr
(Ramesh Chandra)
for Secretary to the Cabinet.
All Members of the Council of Ministers.
Copy forwarded to the Deputy Chairman, Planning
Commission, for information.
Copy forwarded to the Special Assistant to the Prime
Minister/the Principal Private Secretary to the Prime Minister,
Copy forwarded to the Secretary to the President/the
Private Secretary to the Vice-President, for information.
Namshchandr
(Ramesh Chandra)
Under Secretary to the Cabinet,
Copy forwarded to all Secretaries to the Government of
India/Chairman, Railway Board/Joint Secretary, Planning
Commission.
*Copy forwarded to all Ministries of the Government of
India/resident's Secretariat/Vice-President Secretariat/
Department of Atomic Energy/Department of Parliamentary Affairs/
Planning Commission/Prime Minister's Secretariat/Lok Sabha
Secretariat/Rajya Sabha Secretariat, for information.
Duneskehand
(Ramesh Chandra)
Under Secretary to the Cabinet.
P.T.O.
